It looks like that https://webqa-ci.mozilla.com/ is no longer a valid URL. If we want to continue with optional basic authentication we should use the following URL instead:

http://www.mozqa.com/data/mozqa.com/http_auth/basic/

@Nebelhom, do you want to get this fixed?

PR #358 has been shown that coverage doesn't really work. This might be related to the unittest framework we make use of. Maybe we should switch away from that and better use nose or even pytest to run our tests.

https://testrun.org/tox/latest/example/pytest.html

@Motwani, as you told on the other issue you are interested to work on it?
